__Sibe MardeÅ¡iÄ‡__ is a Croatian [[topology|topologist]], retired Professor at the University of Zagreb and a full member of Croatian Academy of Arts and Sciences (HAZU). His son Pavao MardeÅ¡iÄ‡ is also a mathematician, a specialist in the theory of (low dimensional) dynamical systems.

A brief biography can be found in the article [HAPPY 80-th BIRTHDAY PROFESSOR MARDEÅ IÄ†](http://web.math.hr/glasnik/vol_42/mardesic.html), in Glasnik MatematiÄki, the journal that he helped to found.


Most of Sibe MardeÅ¡iÄ‡'s important works are related to [[shape theory]] and geometric topology, mainly in the approach via inverse systems, which he pioneered (there was also a parallel development by [[Tim Porter]]). Sibe MardeÅ¡iÄ‡ wrote several monographs and edited several proceedings volumes in geometric topology and shape theory.  
 
